news1 title: How Ukrainians View This Perilous Moment
news1 abstract: A Russian invasion of the former Soviet state may be imminent. How will Ukraine’s citizens respond if it happens?
news2 title: Was It Me? Or My Teeth?
news2 abstract: In America, a smile is like a résumé. I was afraid mine wasn’t closing the deal.
news3 abstract: David Steinberg’s Sunday puzzle hits us in a sweet spot.
news4 abstract: After the U.S. withdrawal and with their country’s economy collapsing, countless Afghans are trying to escape. Who does the West consider worthy of saving?
news5 abstract: For some couples on the brink of divorce, taking the illegal psychedelic drug was a last resort — but it ended up being the only thing that worked.
news6 title: Why Claiming British Identity Is Complicated
news6 abstract: A scandal in 2014, known as the Trojan Horse affair, exposed what it’s like living in Britain as a British Pakistani.
news7 title: How Being Inclusive Can Be Insulting
news7 abstract: We shouldn’t pretend that a piece of music by a Black artist is classical if it isn’t.
news8 title: My Family Never Asked to Be ‘Liberated’
news9 abstract: A new recipe for eintopf from Yewande Komolafe, and more recipes for both cold and warmer weather.
news10 abstract: Crisis and fashion collide at Moschino and Prada.
